WEBVTT

00:01.349 --> 00:02.872
- Previously on
"God Friended Me"...

00:02.915 --> 00:06.136
A few days ago, someone
calling themselves God

00:06.180 --> 00:07.964
on Facebook started sending me

00:08.008 --> 00:10.271
random friend suggestions,
like Cara.

00:10.314 --> 00:11.750
- You wanna figure out
who's screwing with you,

00:11.794 --> 00:13.622
I'm a journalist,
I know how to find people.

00:13.665 --> 00:15.972
Maybe we'll do some
good in the process.

00:16.016 --> 00:18.105
- That wouldn't be so bad.
My father's a reverend.

00:18.148 --> 00:20.368
We got the whole Luke/Vader
dynamic going on.

00:20.411 --> 00:24.067
You wanna talk about baseball?
- I wanna talk about anything.

00:24.111 --> 00:25.982
- The only one side of
conversation that we're having

00:26.026 --> 00:27.201
is this one,
and you would know that

00:27.244 --> 00:29.072
if you listened
to my podcast.

00:29.116 --> 00:31.901
My sister Ali, he really wants
us to be a family again.

00:31.944 --> 00:32.945
- What is it gonna take to
bring the two of you

00:32.989 --> 00:34.382
back together?

00:34.425 --> 00:35.992
- I'm just not good
at relationships.

00:36.036 --> 00:38.386
- Now that you find
someone you actually like,

00:38.429 --> 00:39.517
you're scared you're
gonna screw it up.

00:39.561 --> 00:41.084
- I put my two weeks in.

00:41.128 --> 00:42.303
I'm finally getting out
of this place.

00:42.346 --> 00:44.000
- I know what's best
for your show.

00:44.044 --> 00:46.089
- It's not what's best
for me right now.

00:46.133 --> 00:49.223
I'm ready to have
a real conversation.

00:49.266 --> 00:51.094
Are you?

00:52.965 --> 00:56.926
[AJR's "Sober Up" playing]

00:56.969 --> 00:58.536
- ♪ Hello, hello

00:58.580 --> 01:01.104
♪ I'm not where
I'm supposed to be ♪

01:01.148 --> 01:03.933
♪ I hope that you're
missing me ♪

01:03.976 --> 01:06.370
♪ 'Cause it makes me
feel young ♪

01:06.414 --> 01:09.112
♪ Won't you help me
sober up ♪

01:09.156 --> 01:11.506
♪ All the big kids,
they got drunk ♪

01:11.549 --> 01:13.812
- "Sell out"?

01:13.856 --> 01:16.076
"Hypocrite"?

01:16.119 --> 01:18.078
♪

01:18.121 --> 01:20.123
I lost half my listeners?

01:20.167 --> 01:22.256
What the...?

01:22.299 --> 01:23.866
- ♪ How's it go again

01:25.302 --> 01:26.825
- Bro, you got some seriously
pissed off atheists

01:26.869 --> 01:28.000
on your hands.
Like, what happened in

01:28.044 --> 01:29.393
your last podcast?
You interview the pope

01:29.437 --> 01:31.265
or something?
- No, no.

01:31.308 --> 01:34.833
I--I talked about how I wanted
to start a real conversation,

01:34.877 --> 01:37.401
and this was their reaction.

01:37.445 --> 01:39.099
- "Hope you burn in hell."

01:39.142 --> 01:41.144
That's a mixed message
for an atheist.

01:41.188 --> 01:43.755
- Dude, I gave up the job of
a lifetime at Frequency

01:43.799 --> 01:47.759
to do my own thing, build
my podcast into something real.

01:47.803 --> 01:49.326
Now, how am I ever
gonna do that

01:49.370 --> 01:51.589
when I can't even hang on to
the listeners I already have?

01:51.633 --> 01:54.549
- Uh, Miles, I'm gonna need you
to head down to HR

01:54.592 --> 01:57.856
at some point
and fill out all new paperwork.

01:57.900 --> 01:59.554
- What're you talking about?

01:59.597 --> 02:01.469
- You gave your
two weeks' notice, remember?

02:01.512 --> 02:04.080
Technically, you need
to be re-hired.

02:04.124 --> 02:06.604
Oh, and, uh,
set aside a Saturday

02:06.648 --> 02:10.173
for new employee
orientation.

02:10.217 --> 02:14.308
Welcome back to iDentitySeal.

02:14.351 --> 02:16.745
- I really hate Phil.

02:16.788 --> 02:19.574
- I'm gonna be working here for
the rest of my life, aren't I?

02:19.617 --> 02:21.924
[cell phone buzzes]

02:24.100 --> 02:26.058
Oh, you gotta be kidding me.
- What?

02:26.102 --> 02:28.626
- God likes tacos?
- You love tacos.

02:28.670 --> 02:30.237
God account knows everything
about you, man.

02:30.280 --> 02:32.064
- Can you be serious
for one second?

02:32.108 --> 02:33.675
This is the first time
the account has sent us

02:33.718 --> 02:35.111
a like of something
- What do you think it means?

02:35.155 --> 02:36.504
- I don't know, but we're
gonna go down there

02:36.547 --> 02:37.983
and figure it out.
- Oh, oh, we are?

02:38.027 --> 02:39.942
- Yes, everything was great
until the God account

02:39.985 --> 02:41.639
came crashing down on me.

02:41.683 --> 02:43.598
Now I need to get
my life back together.

02:43.641 --> 02:46.035
And the only way to do that is
to figure out who's behind this

02:46.078 --> 02:48.777
and put an end to it.
Come on, let's go.

02:48.820 --> 02:52.041
[suspenseful music]

02:52.084 --> 02:54.696
- Good morning, Ali.
- You're out of almond milk.

02:54.739 --> 02:56.567
- Don't you mean,
"We're out of almond milk"?

02:59.091 --> 03:02.007
Oh, I--I cleared out half
the closet for you

03:02.051 --> 03:03.618
while you were
at work last night.

03:03.661 --> 03:05.272
If that isn't love I don't know
what the hell is.

03:05.315 --> 03:06.925
- Is this crazy?

03:06.969 --> 03:08.971
- Moving in together or coffee
without almond milk?

03:09.014 --> 03:11.234
- I told Miles,
but I didn't tell my dad,

03:11.278 --> 03:13.497
and he still thinks I'm
living in the graduate dorm.

03:13.541 --> 03:15.282
- We've been dating
for almost two years.

03:15.325 --> 03:16.892
How surprised do you think
he's gonna be?

03:16.935 --> 03:19.068
- Surprised isn't
the emotion I'm worried about.

03:19.111 --> 03:20.287
- Then what are you
worried about?

03:20.330 --> 03:22.071
- After I came out,

03:22.114 --> 03:24.334
it took him some time to make
his peace with it.

03:24.378 --> 03:27.337
- I know Arthur supports
who you are,

03:27.381 --> 03:29.644
but do you know in the entire
time we've been dating

03:29.687 --> 03:31.646
I've only met him a total
of three times?

03:31.689 --> 03:33.822
- So?
- So,

03:33.865 --> 03:36.172
maybe him supporting who you
are

03:36.216 --> 03:39.001
and engaging with who you are
are two different things.

03:39.044 --> 03:40.785
[rousing music]

03:40.829 --> 03:42.526
You have dinner with him
and Miles tonight, right?

03:42.570 --> 03:44.615
- Mm-hmm, yeah.

03:44.659 --> 03:47.270
- Tell him you moved in
with your girlfriend,

03:47.314 --> 03:50.969
because you're in loving and
committed relationship

03:51.013 --> 03:54.234
and see how he feels about it.

03:54.277 --> 03:58.281
- Okay.
I will.

03:58.325 --> 04:01.241
But not tonight.

04:01.284 --> 04:02.894
- It just posted.

04:02.938 --> 04:04.113
- What did?

04:04.156 --> 04:05.288
- Your last article
is trending

04:05.332 --> 04:07.116
at the top of the
"Catapult" leaderboard.

04:07.159 --> 04:08.683
Top viewed story
two weeks in a row.

04:08.726 --> 04:10.075
What's your secret?

04:10.119 --> 04:12.600
- Cara, Parker.

04:12.643 --> 04:15.124
I wanted to let you know there
might be a senior position

04:15.167 --> 04:17.692
opening in features.
- Really?

04:17.735 --> 04:19.302
- We're a few months
from making any decision,

04:19.346 --> 04:23.306
but I've been thinking
you might be a good fit.

04:23.350 --> 04:25.047
- She remembered my name.

04:25.090 --> 04:26.918
It's progress.

04:26.962 --> 04:29.094
Granted, I've been working here
almost a year, but still.

04:29.138 --> 04:30.966
- A senior position in features

04:31.009 --> 04:32.359
and she thinks
I'd be a good fit?

04:32.402 --> 04:33.969
- You'd crush it in features.

04:34.012 --> 04:36.058
You know what?
We're going out.

04:36.101 --> 04:38.365
Tomorrow night, karaoke.
[cell phone dings]

04:38.408 --> 04:40.497
- Uh, yeah, yeah,
that sounds good.

04:40.541 --> 04:42.238
I have to go.

04:42.282 --> 04:43.892
- Is this that guy who thinks
he's friends with God?

04:43.935 --> 04:45.067
- No, he doesn't
actually think that.

04:45.110 --> 04:46.764
He's an atheist.
I'm just helping him

04:46.808 --> 04:49.027
get to whoever's behind it.
- At a taco truck?

04:49.071 --> 04:50.290
- I go where the stories
take me.

04:50.333 --> 04:52.161
Karaoke, right?
Tomorrow night?

04:52.204 --> 04:55.033
- Yes. And why don't you invite
your professional interest

04:55.077 --> 04:56.774
to join us so I can vet him,

04:56.818 --> 04:57.993
make sure you're not
falling for a Looney Tune.

04:58.036 --> 05:01.039
- I'm not falling for anyone.

05:01.083 --> 05:08.090
♪

05:10.919 --> 05:12.486
[cell phone buzzes]

05:12.529 --> 05:14.792
- Guys, I texted Jaya to
ask her if she wanted to come

05:14.836 --> 05:17.229
meet us down here
for some heavenly tacos.

05:17.273 --> 05:19.057
Her response
is literally "LOL."

05:19.101 --> 05:20.668
- Mm.
[chuckles]

05:20.711 --> 05:22.713
- I'm beginning to feel like
she's not taking me seriously,

05:22.757 --> 05:24.454
like I'm in the friend zone
or something.

05:24.498 --> 05:27.892
I'm gonna need to make a bold
move, make my intentions clear.

05:27.936 --> 05:29.372
- You could tell her.
- Oh.

05:29.416 --> 05:31.069
- When you guys are done
talking about

05:31.113 --> 05:33.376
Rakesh's love life,
I could really use your help.

05:33.420 --> 05:35.117
- I'm starting to sense
this is about

05:35.160 --> 05:37.075
more than just
a taco truck.

05:37.119 --> 05:38.555
- He lost half his podcast
listeners

05:38.599 --> 05:39.904
and now he's blaming
the God account

05:39.948 --> 05:42.080
for getting in his head.
- I'm sorry.

05:42.124 --> 05:44.518
- Yeah.
- Is there anything we can do?

05:44.561 --> 05:46.650
- Let's just find this guy
and tell him I'm out.

05:46.694 --> 05:47.999
I need my life back.

05:48.043 --> 05:49.523
No more God account
screwing stuff up.

05:49.566 --> 05:51.307
- Okay, well,
even if they are here,

05:51.351 --> 05:53.135
how are we gonna flush 'em out?
They could be anyone.

05:53.178 --> 05:54.658
- We could poke 'em.

05:54.702 --> 05:56.094
[suspenseful music]

05:56.138 --> 05:57.661
Like, on Facebook.
We could--we could--

05:57.705 --> 05:59.837
we could poke 'em, and see
if they react on their phone,

05:59.881 --> 06:01.796
and if they do...
- Then we know who they are.

06:01.839 --> 06:04.059
Bro, this is a great idea.

06:04.102 --> 06:06.496
♪

06:06.540 --> 06:08.933
[overlapping chatter]

06:08.977 --> 06:15.070
♪

06:16.724 --> 06:19.422
Whoa. Hey, that kid
just took my wallet.

06:19.466 --> 06:26.429
♪

06:29.563 --> 06:32.087
- Dude, that was crazy, man.
- Did you catch him?

06:32.130 --> 06:33.958
- Just when I thought this day
couldn't get any worse.

06:34.002 --> 06:36.265
- Yo, log into your
iDentitySeal account,

06:36.308 --> 06:39.790
cancel your card, okay?
- Thanks, yes, yes.

06:39.834 --> 06:42.445
- What?

06:42.489 --> 06:44.491
- The God account
liked the taco truck.

06:44.534 --> 06:46.536
I come down here,
poke the account,

06:46.580 --> 06:48.059
basically announcing
that I'm here,

06:48.103 --> 06:50.497
and seconds later this kid
steals my wallet?

06:50.540 --> 06:52.150
- Wait, so you think
the pickpocketing kid

06:52.194 --> 06:53.630
works for
the God account?

06:53.674 --> 06:55.240
- I think any person who's able
to hack into my life

06:55.284 --> 06:56.981
up to this point could pretty
much do whatever they want.

06:57.025 --> 07:00.681
[cell phone buzzes]

07:00.724 --> 07:02.726
Perfect timing.

07:02.770 --> 07:05.947
- Ray Nicolette?

07:05.990 --> 07:08.906
- Forget him.
We gotta find this kid.

07:08.950 --> 07:11.169
- Hey, uh, Miles,
you might wanna see this.

07:11.213 --> 07:13.171
- I don't care about another
friend suggestion, okay?

07:13.215 --> 07:15.739
We find the kid, we find out
who's behind the God account.

07:15.783 --> 07:18.394
- Look what Ray Nicolette
does for a living.

07:18.438 --> 07:19.743
- He's a private investigator?

07:19.787 --> 07:21.266
- Who better
to track someone down?

07:21.310 --> 07:23.747
- That's a good idea.
- Just so we're clear,

07:23.791 --> 07:26.097
you wanna hire one of our
friend's suggestions

07:26.141 --> 07:28.796
to track down the God account.
- I absolutely do.

07:28.839 --> 07:30.101
And when we find him,

07:30.145 --> 07:32.190
we put an end to this
once and for all.

07:38.414 --> 07:41.373
[ominous music]

07:41.417 --> 07:42.505
♪

07:42.549 --> 07:45.987
- Okay, so...

07:46.030 --> 07:48.424
How did you hear about me?

07:48.468 --> 07:51.601
- Uh, we found your name
on the internet.

07:51.645 --> 07:53.777
- Uh, your website hasn't been
updated for a while.

07:53.821 --> 07:55.823
You used to work for the NYPD?

07:55.866 --> 07:57.651
- Twenty years.
Pension allows me

07:57.694 --> 08:00.436
to work when I want,
not work when I don't want,

08:00.480 --> 08:03.657
so, why don't you just tell me
what this is all about

08:03.700 --> 08:04.919
and we'll go from there?

08:04.962 --> 08:06.747
- Well, I was at this
taco truck and some kid

08:06.790 --> 08:09.793
stole my wallet, and we need
you to help us find him.

08:09.837 --> 08:12.230
- You wanna hire
a private investigator

08:12.274 --> 08:15.103
to help find your wallet?
- It was a gift.

08:15.146 --> 08:17.366
[foreboding playful music]

08:17.409 --> 08:19.542
Sentimental value.

08:19.586 --> 08:21.065
♪

08:21.109 --> 08:22.937
- Why don't you
take a swing at it?

08:22.980 --> 08:25.766
- Okay, look, we can give you
a good description of the guy.

08:25.809 --> 08:28.899
And he probably works the area,
might even be in the system.

08:28.943 --> 08:31.249
So all you would have to do
as an ex-cop

08:31.293 --> 08:33.513
is pick up your phone, call up
some of your cop buddies,

08:33.556 --> 08:35.384
and see if our guy rings
any bells.

08:35.427 --> 08:38.256
- Well, you put it that way,
sounds like an easy gig.

08:38.300 --> 08:41.303
Tsk.
[exhales deeply]

08:41.346 --> 08:42.913
You're sure
you don't wanna tell me

08:42.957 --> 08:45.568
what's really going on here?
Might make it a little easier.

08:45.612 --> 08:47.657
- Like I said, we just need you
to help us find the kid

08:47.701 --> 08:50.181
that stole the wallet.
- Sentimental.

08:50.225 --> 08:51.879
- Yep.
- Wallet.

08:51.922 --> 08:54.490
[breathes heavily]

08:54.534 --> 08:56.927
All right.
I'll play along.

08:56.971 --> 08:58.494
For now,

08:58.538 --> 09:00.540
uh, I'm gonna need
a little retainer

09:00.583 --> 09:03.281
in lieu of the truth.

09:03.325 --> 09:05.588
[foreboding music]

09:05.632 --> 09:09.200
- Hi, I am so, so sorry that
I'm late, but I'm here.

09:09.244 --> 09:10.898
Did you order for me?
- Yeah.

09:10.941 --> 09:13.553
Hanger steak, medium rare,
20 minutes ago.

09:13.596 --> 09:15.511
- [whispers]
I'm sorry.

09:15.555 --> 09:17.426
[piano music]

09:17.469 --> 09:19.210
- So how's everything.
- It's good.

09:19.254 --> 09:20.995
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

09:21.038 --> 09:28.045
♪

09:32.659 --> 09:35.444
- Oh, thank God.

09:35.487 --> 09:37.446
- Thank you.

09:37.489 --> 09:39.753
♪

09:39.796 --> 09:42.277
- [clears throat]

09:42.320 --> 09:44.584
♪

09:44.627 --> 09:45.846
Lord, we thank you
for your grace

09:45.889 --> 09:48.588
and for gathering us here
tonight.

09:48.631 --> 09:50.894
♪

09:50.938 --> 09:52.635
Is my giving thanks
interrupting

09:52.679 --> 09:54.245
whatever it is
that you're doing?

09:54.289 --> 09:55.682
- No.
- Oh.

09:55.725 --> 09:57.248
- I take it we're done
with grace.

09:57.292 --> 09:59.511
Okay, amen, let's eat.
- Just so you know,

09:59.555 --> 10:02.253
people from all walks of life,
all faiths,

10:02.297 --> 10:04.734
give thanks for what they have.
- Right. And your point being?

10:04.778 --> 10:06.780
- You don't have to go
out of your way to be rude.

10:06.823 --> 10:09.130
- My salmon looks amazing.

10:09.173 --> 10:12.742
Dad, how's your pasta?
Miles, your steak good?

10:12.786 --> 10:14.309
- It's very good, sweetie.
Thank you.

10:14.352 --> 10:16.180
- Yeah, it looks great.
- Yeah? Good.

10:16.224 --> 10:18.530
- It's very good.

10:18.574 --> 10:20.228
♪

10:20.271 --> 10:23.666
- Mm.

10:23.710 --> 10:26.887
[exhales deeply]

10:26.930 --> 10:29.063
♪

10:29.106 --> 10:32.370
So, our choices are arguing

10:32.414 --> 10:34.242
or deafening silence.

10:34.285 --> 10:35.939
Is that it?
There's nothing

10:35.983 --> 10:38.420
we can talk about?
- Could talk about baseball.

10:38.463 --> 10:41.118
- Or we can talk
about the movies.

10:41.162 --> 10:44.513
"Star Wars," it's a--
it's a classic.

10:44.556 --> 10:48.648
Luke Skywalker battling his
evil father Darth Vader.

10:48.691 --> 10:51.738
[mimics Darth Vader's
heavy breathing]

10:51.781 --> 10:53.522
- Wait, did you
listen to my podcast?

10:53.565 --> 10:55.742
- I did.
- Oh.

10:55.785 --> 10:57.569
Okay, so what did you think?

10:57.613 --> 10:59.920
♪

10:59.963 --> 11:01.312
[clears throat]

11:01.356 --> 11:03.271
I think that

11:03.314 --> 11:06.491
propagating what
you believe is one thing,

11:06.535 --> 11:09.364
mocking other faiths...

11:09.407 --> 11:11.018
- Hmm.
S--

11:11.061 --> 11:12.759
what--what--what're
you talking about?

11:12.802 --> 11:15.152
- Oh, come on, pretending that
you've been friended by God.

11:15.196 --> 11:17.328
I mean, do your followers
think that's funny?

11:17.372 --> 11:18.634
- My followers, well...

11:18.678 --> 11:20.244
A lot of my followers
have jumped ship,

11:20.288 --> 11:23.378
so I guess your prayers
have been answered.

11:23.421 --> 11:25.249
My podcast is failing.

11:25.293 --> 11:26.686
- My prayers? I mean,
what do you think, that I--

11:26.729 --> 11:30.211
- I'm moving in with Dee.

11:30.254 --> 11:32.039
♪

11:32.082 --> 11:35.912
And when I say "moving,"
I mean "moved."

11:35.956 --> 11:37.261
Past tense.

11:37.305 --> 11:39.263
- You're living together?

11:39.307 --> 11:41.788
- Yeah, it just--it just
sort of happened.

11:41.831 --> 11:43.659
♪

11:43.703 --> 11:47.358
- You knew about this too?

11:47.402 --> 11:52.102
Moving in with someone
does not just sort of happen.

11:52.146 --> 11:54.278
Why didn't you
tell me about it?

11:54.322 --> 11:56.716
- I'm telling you now, Dad.

11:56.759 --> 11:58.195
♪

11:58.239 --> 12:01.111
- Mm-hmm.

12:01.155 --> 12:03.331
All right.

12:03.374 --> 12:04.985
♪

12:05.028 --> 12:07.335
Whatever makes you happy.

12:07.378 --> 12:09.250
- Really?
- Really?

12:09.293 --> 12:12.949
- Mm-hmm.

12:12.993 --> 12:15.256
- I'm sorry that I didn't talk
to you about this,

12:15.299 --> 12:16.648
but can we talk about it?

12:16.692 --> 12:18.738
- There's nothing
to talk about.

12:18.781 --> 12:23.046
Like I said,
whatever makes you happy.

12:23.090 --> 12:25.222
Here.

12:25.266 --> 12:27.224
To new beginnings.

12:27.268 --> 12:30.227
[ominous music]

12:30.271 --> 12:37.278
♪

12:41.456 --> 12:43.066
- Here you go.

12:43.110 --> 12:45.199
- Ooh, how much do we owe you?
- No, it's my treat.

12:45.242 --> 12:46.722
Since you don't have a wallet.

12:46.766 --> 12:49.246
- Not a single cinnamon raisin
in the bunch.

12:49.290 --> 12:51.335
How purist.
I like your style.

12:51.379 --> 12:53.773
- Back at ya.
Speaking of style,

12:53.816 --> 12:56.819
have you figured out
your grand romantic gesture

12:56.863 --> 12:59.604
to win Jaya over?
- No, not yet.

12:59.648 --> 13:01.476
Wait, let me--let--
can I ask you something?

13:01.519 --> 13:05.262
So, what is
the most romantic gesture

13:05.306 --> 13:07.221
a guy's ever
done for you?

13:07.264 --> 13:09.179
- It's kind of personal.
[chuckles]

13:09.223 --> 13:11.355
- Uh, fine, hypothetical.

13:11.399 --> 13:13.705
What would sweep Cara Bloom
off her feet?

13:13.749 --> 13:15.882
I'm kind of desperate here.

13:15.925 --> 13:19.407
- Yeah, come on,
help the guy out.

13:19.450 --> 13:20.800
- [exhales]

13:20.843 --> 13:24.020
Okay, um...

13:24.064 --> 13:27.502
All I know is that it wouldn't
be some over-the-top message

13:27.545 --> 13:30.374
on a jumbotron type of thing.

13:30.418 --> 13:32.376
Just gotta come from the heart.

13:32.420 --> 13:35.727
Be honest and vulnerable and
let her know you're the one.

13:35.771 --> 13:37.817
♪

13:37.860 --> 13:40.297
- So how much would this
jumbotron idea cost again?

13:40.341 --> 13:41.733
- [chuckles]

13:41.777 --> 13:44.214
- Okay. Please tell me
that you've heard from Ray

13:44.258 --> 13:46.260
so we can talk about
literally anything else.

13:46.303 --> 13:48.566
- No, not yet.
- Well, I did do some digging.

13:48.610 --> 13:50.220
- On Ray? Why?

13:50.264 --> 13:51.874
- Well, he's still
our friend suggestion.

13:51.918 --> 13:53.833
Like, he doesn't have much
of a digital footprint,

13:53.876 --> 13:56.052
no friends or family,
except for his wife,

13:56.096 --> 13:57.706
but she died last year.

13:57.749 --> 13:59.403
His Facebook hasn't
been updated since.

13:59.447 --> 14:02.363
Well, I was thinking,
we could go analog.

14:02.406 --> 14:04.626
Follow him around today,
see where he goes.

14:04.669 --> 14:06.323
Could uncover how we're
supposed to help him.

14:06.367 --> 14:07.977
- I appreciate what you're
trying to do,

14:08.021 --> 14:11.024
but I just want him to help us
find the God account.

14:11.067 --> 14:14.984
- Why can't we do both?
- She's got you there, bro.

14:15.028 --> 14:18.248
- Come on.
We've never tailed anyone.

14:18.292 --> 14:21.077
We could get baseball hats,
sunglasses,

14:21.121 --> 14:23.601
go full spy.
It'll be fun.

14:23.645 --> 14:25.690
♪

14:25.734 --> 14:29.085
- [chuckles]
Fine.

14:29.129 --> 14:32.480
♪

14:32.523 --> 14:35.483
[foreboding music]

14:35.526 --> 14:42.533
♪

14:53.327 --> 15:00.421
♪

15:12.520 --> 15:15.479
[pensive music]

15:15.523 --> 15:21.572
♪

15:21.616 --> 15:24.575
- [blows]

15:24.619 --> 15:31.234
♪

15:42.419 --> 15:44.421
- This place must be
important for him.

15:44.465 --> 15:46.423
- Yeah, what do you
think it means?

15:46.467 --> 15:49.557
- Boy, you two are
really bad at this.

15:49.600 --> 15:51.820
- Uh, heh--hey, Ray.

15:51.863 --> 15:53.561
- Okay, new rules.

15:53.604 --> 15:55.998
You want me to help you?

15:56.042 --> 15:58.566
It's time you told me the truth
of what's really going on here.

15:58.609 --> 16:00.916
[tense music]

16:07.488 --> 16:10.056
- Okay, you're telling me
you were friended

16:10.099 --> 16:11.622
by God on Facebook?

16:11.666 --> 16:12.972
- No, I'm telling you someone

16:13.015 --> 16:14.538
calling themselves God
friended me.

16:14.582 --> 16:16.627
- And you think the kid that
lifted your wallet

16:16.671 --> 16:18.020
is somehow involved with him?

16:18.064 --> 16:20.196
- Look, I don't think random
coincidences

16:20.240 --> 16:22.111
are a way to explain
what's been happening to me.

16:22.155 --> 16:24.331
Now, if he's connected
and we can find him,

16:24.374 --> 16:26.333
maybe he can lead us to
whoever's behind this.

16:26.376 --> 16:28.944
- I've heard crazier.
- You have?

16:28.988 --> 16:30.641
- I was a cop for 20 years.
You know how many people

16:30.685 --> 16:32.382
told me they could talk to God?

16:32.426 --> 16:35.342
The social media thing's new.
I'll give you that.

16:35.385 --> 16:39.172
All right, a--assuming I accept
all this at face value,

16:39.215 --> 16:41.957
I mean, it seems pretty benign.

16:42.001 --> 16:43.567
Why not delete it
or just ignore it?

16:43.611 --> 16:45.613
- Because, A, they won't stop,
and B, I wanna know

16:45.656 --> 16:48.050
who's behind it before I do.
Now can you help us?

16:48.094 --> 16:51.053
Please.
- Can I?

16:51.097 --> 16:53.186
Come on, guys, I've been around
long enough to know

16:53.229 --> 16:55.840
when a piece
of the story is missing.

16:57.712 --> 17:00.367
There's a reason you came to me
specifically, isn't there?

17:06.503 --> 17:08.331
I always hated that picture.

17:08.375 --> 17:10.464
And hey, let me save us all
some time, okay?

17:10.507 --> 17:11.943
I don't need any help.

17:11.987 --> 17:14.076
- Yeah, well, no one
ever really does.

17:14.120 --> 17:17.645
Not at first.

17:17.688 --> 17:21.170
- Well, I made some calls and
got a match on your pickpocket,

17:21.214 --> 17:25.218
so I guess we might as well
play this record to the end.

17:25.261 --> 17:28.177
Isaac Delgado, 15,
he was picked up in the area

17:28.221 --> 17:30.875
for some petty things.
Okay, he's a minor,

17:30.919 --> 17:32.181
which means his records
are sealed,

17:32.225 --> 17:33.748
but he lives with his mother.

17:33.791 --> 17:36.316
I should be able to get
her address downtown.

17:36.359 --> 17:39.319
[cell phone buzzes]

17:39.362 --> 17:40.624
[suspenseful music]

17:40.668 --> 17:41.886
- You think
I can meet you there?

17:41.930 --> 17:44.063
I have to handle something.
- Yeah, sure.

17:44.106 --> 17:46.369
Nancy Drew and I will get the
address and text it to you.

17:46.413 --> 17:48.458
- Nancy Drew, really?

17:48.502 --> 17:51.592
- [sighs]

17:51.635 --> 17:54.290
- Being a private investigator
must be exciting.

17:54.334 --> 17:58.120
- You know the difference
a P.I. and a peeping tom?

17:58.164 --> 17:59.817
Fifty bucks a day
plus expenses.

17:59.861 --> 18:02.211
- [chuckles]
So why do it?

18:02.255 --> 18:04.648
- Eh, after I retired
from the force,

18:04.692 --> 18:07.521
I got my license just so I'd
have something to do,

18:07.564 --> 18:10.132
but, uh,
[clears throat]

18:10.176 --> 18:11.916
Abby worked.
We were never lucky enough

18:11.960 --> 18:14.049
to have kids,
and all of a sudden

18:14.093 --> 18:16.921
I got nothing but time
on my hands.

18:16.965 --> 18:19.010
- Can I ask you something?
- Mm-hmm.

18:19.054 --> 18:21.578
- That, uh--that flower you
left at the bridge,

18:21.622 --> 18:25.147
that was for her?

18:25.191 --> 18:28.455
- Yeah.
Yeah.

18:28.498 --> 18:31.240
She passed away a year ago.

18:31.284 --> 18:35.418
You know, uh...

18:35.462 --> 18:39.422
It's weird how a single year

18:39.466 --> 18:42.773
can feel like forever
and just yesterday

18:42.817 --> 18:44.949
all at the same time.

18:44.993 --> 18:47.474
[solemn piano music]

18:47.517 --> 18:49.606
♪

18:49.650 --> 18:51.869
Anyway, that was our spot.

18:51.913 --> 18:54.045
I go there sometimes

18:54.089 --> 18:56.178
and just talk to her.

18:56.222 --> 19:00.182
Don't worry, I'm not crazy,
she doesn't talk back.

19:00.226 --> 19:02.053
- What was she like?

19:02.097 --> 19:05.492
- Abby was, uh,
she was a social worker.

19:05.535 --> 19:07.972
I mean, quintessential too.
I never seen anybody

19:08.016 --> 19:11.976
more dedicated
to helping people.

19:12.020 --> 19:14.109
Enough of me, what about you?

19:14.153 --> 19:15.980
- What do you mean?

19:16.024 --> 19:17.939
- All right, well, you told me
Miles got the friend request

19:17.982 --> 19:19.897
that helped reunite you
with your mother,

19:19.941 --> 19:22.900
so, why are you still
helping him?

19:22.944 --> 19:25.076
I mean, why stick around?
- Well, I'm a journalist.

19:25.120 --> 19:27.209
I'd be crazy to walk away
from a story like this.

19:27.253 --> 19:29.080
- I see.

19:29.124 --> 19:32.214
So you're hanging out with
this guy because of the story.

19:32.258 --> 19:35.217
[introspective music]

19:35.261 --> 19:37.219
♪

19:37.263 --> 19:39.308
- Miles.
Wow.

19:39.352 --> 19:41.528
Um,

19:41.571 --> 19:44.835
what're you doing here?

19:44.879 --> 19:48.230
- Um, I wanted to talk
to you about Ali.

19:48.274 --> 19:49.666
- Ah.

19:49.710 --> 19:51.494
- About what happened
at dinner.

19:51.538 --> 19:54.062
Look, I know you were hurt
because Ali moved in with Dee

19:54.105 --> 19:55.933
without telling you.
- She is an adult.

19:55.977 --> 19:57.631
She makes her own decisions.
- Oh, come on, Dad.

19:57.674 --> 19:59.372
I thought you guys had a close
relationship,

19:59.415 --> 20:02.070
that you talked about things,
especially important things.

20:02.113 --> 20:03.419
- Well, so did I,
but apparently

20:03.463 --> 20:05.029
my relationship with my
daughter is no better

20:05.073 --> 20:08.250
than my relationship
with m--my son.

20:08.294 --> 20:11.253
[stirring music]

20:11.297 --> 20:13.864
♪

20:13.908 --> 20:17.694
- Then change it.

20:17.738 --> 20:19.392
Ali wants to talk
to you about this.

20:19.435 --> 20:21.263
- No, look, if she wanted to
talk to me, she would have.

20:21.307 --> 20:23.570
- Maybe she doesn't know how.
Maybe she doesn't know how

20:23.613 --> 20:27.226
to navigate this part of her
life with you.

20:27.269 --> 20:29.967
Maybe neither one of you do.

20:30.011 --> 20:33.232
♪

20:33.275 --> 20:36.844
But the good thing is,
is that it's never too late.

20:36.887 --> 20:39.020
- Mm, well,

20:39.063 --> 20:41.805
I'd like to believe that,
but...

20:41.849 --> 20:44.678
♪

20:44.721 --> 20:46.288
- All right, well,
I should get going.

20:46.332 --> 20:49.160
- Of course.
Oh, did Ali ask you

20:49.204 --> 20:50.074
to come down here
to talk to me?

20:50.118 --> 20:51.989
- No.

20:52.033 --> 20:55.819
I figured after all the time
she's come to you on my behalf,

20:55.863 --> 20:57.995
I owed her one.

20:58.039 --> 20:59.997
- Hmm.

21:00.041 --> 21:01.912
♪

21:01.956 --> 21:03.740
Hmm.

21:03.784 --> 21:07.135
[cell phone dings, buzzes]

21:14.229 --> 21:16.100
- Hey, you remember me?
If not,

21:16.144 --> 21:18.755
check my driver's license.

21:18.799 --> 21:20.322
- Let's go get your mom.
We can all have

21:20.366 --> 21:23.543
a nice little
chat here, huh?

21:23.586 --> 21:26.154
- I don't think
that'll be necessary.

21:26.197 --> 21:27.416
I don't got your wallet, man.

21:27.460 --> 21:29.810
I tossed it after
I took the cash.

21:29.853 --> 21:32.856
And by "cash" I mean, $4?
- All right, forget the wallet.

21:32.900 --> 21:34.336
You tell me who told you
to take it.

21:34.380 --> 21:36.512
- Hey, I'm a retired cop, kid.

21:36.556 --> 21:38.732
And you just admitted to theft.

21:38.775 --> 21:40.777
That plus being a Jets fan,
that's all I need to call

21:40.821 --> 21:43.998
my cop buddies down here
to haul your ass downtown,

21:44.041 --> 21:45.608
cause a whole lot of
unnecessary grief

21:45.652 --> 21:47.349
for your mother.

21:47.393 --> 21:50.787
Or you can give us a name.
- I never got a name, okay?

21:50.831 --> 21:52.572
They just told me to snatch
your wallet

21:52.615 --> 21:54.400
and take it to some building.
- Who? Who--who--

21:54.443 --> 21:55.836
- What did they look like and
why did they tell you

21:55.879 --> 21:57.403
to take it?
- I just took the money.

21:57.446 --> 21:59.100
Didn't ask any questions.
- Building, building,

21:59.143 --> 22:01.972
what building?
Come on, we need an address.

22:02.016 --> 22:05.062
- 32 West 17th Street.

22:05.106 --> 22:08.675
Took it to the third floor.
That's all I know, I swear.

22:08.718 --> 22:11.678
[suspenseful music]

22:11.721 --> 22:13.636
♪

22:13.680 --> 22:15.246
- Cool, so what's
the plan here?

22:15.290 --> 22:17.814
- We knock on the door.
I tell whoever's behind this

22:17.858 --> 22:20.643
to stop all of it.

22:20.687 --> 22:22.515
- Yeah, he's never
been big on plans.

22:22.558 --> 22:26.432
- So I gather.

22:26.475 --> 22:28.259
- You've gotta be kidding me.

22:28.303 --> 22:31.306
- Sorry, kid.
We been played.

22:38.357 --> 22:40.315
- He lied to us.

22:40.359 --> 22:43.231
[suspenseful music]

22:43.274 --> 22:46.016
- I'm almost impressed.

22:46.060 --> 22:48.149
Kid's good under pressure.
I'll give him that.

22:48.192 --> 22:49.672
- All right, well, we're gonna
go back and talk to him.

22:49.716 --> 22:51.935
Call up your cop buddies.
- That's a waste of time.

22:51.979 --> 22:53.415
- Why?

22:53.459 --> 22:54.416
- I saw the look in his eyes
when I threatened to call

22:54.460 --> 22:56.157
the cops before.
He was scared.

22:56.200 --> 22:58.464
So he told us what
we wanted to hear.

22:58.507 --> 22:59.856
That's all he's got.

22:59.900 --> 23:00.944
- Well, I still need to figure
out who's behind this.

23:00.988 --> 23:02.163
- That seems
like a "you" problem.

23:02.206 --> 23:03.904
- No, they sent us
your name too.

23:03.947 --> 23:05.471
Aren't you
the least bit curious?

23:05.514 --> 23:08.691
- Look, I have no idea why
anybody sent you my name,

23:08.735 --> 23:11.999
but if all this account wants
you to do is help people,

23:12.042 --> 23:14.741
[grunts] what's it matter
who's behind it?

23:14.784 --> 23:19.310
Help or don't help.
It ain't a tough choice, kid.

23:19.354 --> 23:21.356
- Hey, wha--what about
our retainer?

23:21.400 --> 23:23.706
- Sorry, no refunds.

23:23.750 --> 23:27.144
♪

23:27.188 --> 23:28.537
[door knocks]

23:31.540 --> 23:35.326
- Hello, Dee, um, I hope it's
okay that I dropped by, uh...

23:37.154 --> 23:39.766
- You're welcome any time.

23:39.809 --> 23:43.117
I'll go get Ali.
- Okay.

23:43.160 --> 23:45.380
Oh, uh, a housewarming gift.

23:45.424 --> 23:48.296
Um, pasta strainer.

23:48.339 --> 23:50.472
Top of the line.
I don't know.

23:50.516 --> 23:53.301
- Thank you.

23:53.344 --> 23:56.304
- I thought that
we talked about stuff,

23:56.347 --> 23:58.132
that we had that kind of
relationship.

23:58.175 --> 24:00.395
- I know, Dad, me too.

24:00.439 --> 24:03.050
And we do talk about stuff.

24:03.093 --> 24:05.400
- Just not this.

24:05.444 --> 24:08.316
- Well, I wanted to,
but...

24:08.359 --> 24:10.405
- What?

24:10.449 --> 24:12.842
- I don't know, I just--I felt
like we we've always

24:12.886 --> 24:16.542
had this unspoken thing
between us,

24:16.585 --> 24:19.022
where you would ask
how things were going.

24:19.066 --> 24:21.460
I'd tell you fine,

24:21.503 --> 24:23.331
but I'd leave out the details,

24:23.374 --> 24:26.290
and I didn't talk about
this part of my life.

24:26.334 --> 24:29.293
And Dad, you never asked.

24:29.337 --> 24:32.775
- It's not what I want.

24:32.819 --> 24:34.864
It's just that after
your mother died,

24:34.908 --> 24:36.649
I knew that there would be
things

24:36.692 --> 24:38.564
that I wouldn't be
prepared for,

24:38.607 --> 24:41.349
things that

24:41.392 --> 24:43.351
she was gonna take care of.

24:45.222 --> 24:46.789
I just didn't know
there would be so many,

24:46.833 --> 24:49.357
and that I would be bad
at all of them.

24:49.400 --> 24:51.751
[stirring music]

24:51.794 --> 24:54.623
Part of me knows

24:54.667 --> 24:58.584
I don't have much to offer

24:58.627 --> 25:00.934
this part of your life.

25:00.977 --> 25:03.284
- Dad.

25:03.327 --> 25:04.677
Look,

25:04.720 --> 25:08.724
I don't need you
to offer me anything.

25:08.768 --> 25:11.466
I just need you
to be here for it.

25:11.510 --> 25:14.425
And let me tell you about it.

25:14.469 --> 25:16.863
- I would like that very much.

25:16.906 --> 25:18.560
- [chuckles]

25:18.604 --> 25:20.736
Mm.

25:20.780 --> 25:23.347
But wait,
if you don't mind me asking,

25:23.391 --> 25:25.480
what prompted this amazing

25:25.524 --> 25:27.308
Arthur Finer
self-reflection?

25:27.351 --> 25:30.180
- Your brother.
He came to see me.

25:30.224 --> 25:31.573
- He did?
- Mm-hmm.

25:31.617 --> 25:34.750
Turns out that, um,
we agree on one thing.

25:34.794 --> 25:37.187
♪

25:37.231 --> 25:39.407
You.

25:39.450 --> 25:41.583
- Mm.

25:41.627 --> 25:44.586
["Make Me Feel" playing]

25:44.630 --> 25:45.935
[cheering]

25:45.979 --> 25:47.894
- Next up to the mic, Jaya.

25:47.937 --> 25:50.244
- ♪ You got me right here
in your jean pocket ♪

25:50.287 --> 25:51.985
♪

25:52.028 --> 25:54.378
♪ Laying your body
on a shag carpet ♪

25:54.422 --> 25:56.293
♪

25:56.337 --> 25:58.861
♪ You know I love it
so please don't stop it ♪

25:58.905 --> 26:00.907
- You're still thinking about
what happened today with Isaac?

26:00.950 --> 26:04.563
- Isaac, Ray, the podcast,
listeners leaving me.

26:05.607 --> 26:08.479
Isaac steals my wallet, and
then we get a friend suggestion

26:08.523 --> 26:10.133
for a private detective?

26:10.177 --> 26:11.831
- And you think there's
a connection between them?

26:11.874 --> 26:15.617
- Maybe. Did Ray say
anything to you today?

26:15.661 --> 26:19.186
- Uh, he mainly just
talked about his wife.

26:19.229 --> 26:21.841
You know, she's been gone
almost a year

26:21.884 --> 26:26.541
and he still goes to the
Bow Bridge just to talk to her.

26:26.585 --> 26:29.022
Maybe we're supposed to help
him get over his loss?

26:29.065 --> 26:32.503
- Maybe we are, but how?
[cell phone buzzes]

26:32.547 --> 26:35.463
It's an alert from
my iDentitySeal account.

26:35.506 --> 26:38.553
Looks like Isaac tried to make
a couple of purchases

26:38.597 --> 26:40.642
before I cancelled my card.

26:40.686 --> 26:43.166
- ♪ That's just the way
you make me feel ♪

26:43.210 --> 26:45.342
[cheers and applause]

26:45.386 --> 26:46.648
Oh, my God,
that was so much fun.

26:46.692 --> 26:48.171
- Yeah.

26:48.215 --> 26:50.173
- Have you picked
your song out yet?

26:50.217 --> 26:52.611
- I'm not really a singer,
so... [chuckles]

26:52.654 --> 26:54.525
- Oh, okay.

26:54.569 --> 26:56.397
It's no big deal.
[cell phone dings]

26:56.440 --> 26:59.400
[dance music]

26:59.443 --> 27:00.793
[laughs]

27:00.836 --> 27:02.316
- What's so funny?
- Oh, nothing.

27:02.359 --> 27:04.144
It's just some of my friends.

27:04.187 --> 27:07.713
Actually, would you mind
if I invited them?

27:07.756 --> 27:09.497
- Here?

27:09.540 --> 27:11.978
Now?
- They love karaoke.

27:12.021 --> 27:14.284
I'm gonna go look at
the song list again.

27:14.328 --> 27:19.333
♪

27:19.376 --> 27:21.509
- You good?

27:21.552 --> 27:23.293
- Man, we're supposed
to be on a date

27:23.337 --> 27:24.991
and now she's calling
her friends here

27:25.034 --> 27:27.471
and I don't know what to do.

27:27.515 --> 27:31.780
- I meant, did you
need anything else?

27:31.824 --> 27:34.827
- I'll do one more of these.

27:34.870 --> 27:37.786
- A lot of household things.
Grocery store, drug store,

27:37.830 --> 27:39.614
no high end electronics
or clothing.

27:39.658 --> 27:41.007
It's weird.
- Wait, wait, wait.

27:41.050 --> 27:44.227
Stop right there.
- "JPay, NY City, and DOC."

27:44.271 --> 27:45.925
What's that?
- Yeah, JPay, it's a--

27:45.968 --> 27:48.318
it's a service used to wire
money to people in prison.

27:48.362 --> 27:50.538
It doesn't say on the charge
who he sent the money to.

27:50.581 --> 27:52.061
How can we find that out?

27:52.105 --> 27:54.063
- Well, luckily we still have

27:54.107 --> 27:56.631
an ex-police officer
on retainer.

27:56.675 --> 27:58.720
- Sorry I'm late.
No excuses.

27:58.764 --> 28:01.723
- Parker, this is Miles.
Miles, Parker.

28:01.767 --> 28:03.899
- Pleasure to meet you.
- Likewise.

28:03.943 --> 28:07.337
- Uh, sorry,
I have to make a call.

28:07.381 --> 28:08.643
- [hisses]
Yeah.

28:08.687 --> 28:10.558
- The God account my ass.
He's hot.

28:10.601 --> 28:13.213
[chuckles]

28:13.256 --> 28:15.606
- Hey, hey, Ray.

28:15.650 --> 28:17.913
Yeah, it's Miles.
Hey, can--can you please

28:17.957 --> 28:19.480
do me one more favor?

28:19.523 --> 28:21.612
- About to sit down to my
famous homemade lasagna

28:21.656 --> 28:23.658
and a nice glass of Chianti.
What? You're killing me.

28:23.702 --> 28:25.529
- Come on, Ray,
it's important.

28:25.573 --> 28:28.489
Okay, one of the charges that
Isaac made to my credit card

28:28.532 --> 28:30.491
was a money transfer to JPay,

28:30.534 --> 28:32.145
but the prisoner's name
wasn't on it.

28:32.188 --> 28:34.756
- Well, there should be
a seven-digit NYSID number

28:34.800 --> 28:36.671
attached to the charge.

28:36.715 --> 28:39.761
- If I text you the number,
can you give me the name?

28:39.805 --> 28:41.937
- [sighs] Yeah, I guess
I could call a buddy

28:41.981 --> 28:43.634
in the DOC.

28:43.678 --> 28:47.595
I'm gonna charge you, though,
if my lasagna goes cold.

28:47.638 --> 28:50.772
- Look, whatever you're
thinking, you're wrong.

28:50.816 --> 28:52.774
I can't hang out with someone
just because they're cute?

28:52.818 --> 28:54.645
- So you admit he's cute.

28:54.689 --> 28:56.430
- Why am I friends with you?

28:56.473 --> 28:58.606
- Because you need someone who
doesn't overthink everything.

28:58.649 --> 28:59.912
- That's your pitch?
I should listen to you

28:59.955 --> 29:01.696
because you don't think
about things?

29:01.740 --> 29:04.568
- You should listen to me
because you like him.

29:04.612 --> 29:06.527
You haven't talked this much
about someone

29:06.570 --> 29:08.181
since cute banker guy.

29:08.224 --> 29:10.313
- Miles and I,
we're just friends.

29:10.357 --> 29:13.273
We like hanging out.
And,

29:13.316 --> 29:16.189
yeah, hanging out has led
to some great stories.

29:16.232 --> 29:19.714
- I see.
- What?

29:19.758 --> 29:21.672
- You're worried that if you go
for it with Miles

29:21.716 --> 29:25.546
and it ends badly,
there goes all those stories.

29:25.589 --> 29:26.852
- [sighs]

29:26.895 --> 29:28.723
- Ray said he's gonna
call me back.

29:28.767 --> 29:29.898
- Who's Ray?

29:29.942 --> 29:33.293
A story you two are working on?

29:33.336 --> 29:35.208
- Hey, where's Rakesh?

29:35.251 --> 29:38.515
He's not back from the bar yet?

29:38.559 --> 29:41.867
- Oh, my goodness.
Rakesh is about to sing.

29:41.910 --> 29:44.521
- Oh, he changed his mind.

29:44.565 --> 29:46.828
♪

29:46.872 --> 29:48.961
What's the big deal?
- No, no, no, you don't get it.

29:49.004 --> 29:51.572
Rakesh does not do karaoke.

29:51.615 --> 29:55.097
- So why is he doing it now?

29:55.141 --> 29:57.534
- Isn't it obvious?

29:57.578 --> 29:59.667
- Next up to the mic, Rakesh.

29:59.710 --> 30:02.061
[mild microphone feedback]
- Uh, hey, hi, guys.

30:02.104 --> 30:03.976
[sharp microphone feedback]
Ooh.

30:04.019 --> 30:06.195
Uh, sorry, um,

30:06.239 --> 30:07.806
you're probably gonna
miss that high-pitched squeal

30:07.849 --> 30:10.765
in about ten seconds.
- [squeals]

30:10.809 --> 30:13.768
["More Than Words Can Say"
playing]

30:13.812 --> 30:14.769
♪

30:14.813 --> 30:17.380
♪ Here I am

30:17.424 --> 30:20.340
♪ Six o'clock in the morning

30:20.383 --> 30:22.516
♪

30:22.559 --> 30:25.867
♪ Still thinking about you

30:25.911 --> 30:28.696
Oh, God.

30:28.739 --> 30:31.133
♪ It's still hard

30:31.177 --> 30:34.441
♪ At six o'clock
in the morning ♪

30:34.484 --> 30:36.225
♪

30:36.269 --> 30:39.141
♪ To sleep without you

30:39.185 --> 30:41.448
♪

30:41.491 --> 30:44.930
♪ And I know that it might

30:44.973 --> 30:49.238
♪ Seem too late for love

30:49.282 --> 30:50.979
♪

30:51.023 --> 30:53.590
♪ I need you now

30:53.634 --> 30:55.897
♪ More than words can say

30:55.941 --> 30:58.900
♪ I need you now

30:58.944 --> 31:00.771
♪

31:00.815 --> 31:02.904
♪ And I've gotta find a way

31:02.948 --> 31:05.646
♪ I need you now

31:05.689 --> 31:07.691
♪

31:07.735 --> 31:09.911
♪ Before I lose my mind

31:09.955 --> 31:12.696
♪ I need you now

31:12.740 --> 31:14.742
♪

31:14.785 --> 31:17.397
♪ Hey, oh, oh, oh

31:17.440 --> 31:20.835
♪ Hey, eh, eh, ey

31:20.879 --> 31:25.274
♪ Too late for love

31:25.318 --> 31:27.102
♪

31:27.146 --> 31:30.323
♪ Can't believe
I'm doing this ♪

31:30.366 --> 31:31.585
♪

31:31.628 --> 31:34.501
Jaya.

31:34.544 --> 31:40.159
♪

31:40.202 --> 31:42.117
I need you now.

31:42.161 --> 31:45.164
[cheers and applause]

31:51.997 --> 31:54.390
- Whoo!

31:54.434 --> 31:56.958
[cell phone buzzing]

31:57.002 --> 31:58.786
[dance music]

31:58.829 --> 32:01.832
- It's Ray.

32:01.876 --> 32:03.182
Hello?

32:03.225 --> 32:05.967
- So what're you gonna do?

32:06.011 --> 32:07.969
Come on.
I was picking up on way more

32:08.013 --> 32:09.840
than a friendship
vibe between you two.

32:09.884 --> 32:13.670
I'm just saying, if it was me,
I'd take the risk.

32:13.714 --> 32:15.934
- Ray just called and said he
knows who Isaac

32:15.977 --> 32:17.674
was sending
money to in prison.

32:17.718 --> 32:19.328
It's his mom.
- But that doesn't make sense.

32:19.372 --> 32:20.764
He's supposed to be living
with his mom.

32:20.808 --> 32:22.462
- Exactly,
so who's he living with?

32:22.505 --> 32:23.942
I think we need
to go down there.

32:23.985 --> 32:25.769
- Okay, yeah.
Uh, I'm so sorry.

32:25.813 --> 32:27.597
- I get it.
Go.

32:27.641 --> 32:29.686
- Okay.

32:29.730 --> 32:32.907
[siren wailing]

32:32.951 --> 32:35.910
[ominous music]

32:35.954 --> 32:37.912
[radio chatter]

32:37.956 --> 32:44.963
♪

32:49.706 --> 32:51.708
- Excuse me, officer.
Could you please tell us

32:51.752 --> 32:53.972
what's going on?
We're friends of Isaac.

32:54.015 --> 32:56.713
- Got a call from ACS.
Kid's been living on his own.

32:56.757 --> 32:58.019
♪

32:58.063 --> 32:59.542
- Ho--how's that possible?

32:59.586 --> 33:01.414
- His mother went to prison
a few months ago,

33:01.457 --> 33:04.460
but nobody knew she was gone
until he tried to wire her

33:04.504 --> 33:05.592
some money with
a stolen credit card.

33:05.635 --> 33:06.985
- So where are you taking him?

33:07.028 --> 33:08.464
- He'll be processed
at the station

33:08.508 --> 33:10.466
and turned over
to Social Services.

33:10.510 --> 33:16.429
♪

33:16.472 --> 33:18.605
- Thank you for seeing us.
We were hoping you could

33:18.648 --> 33:20.476
tell us what's going on
with Isaac Delgado.

33:20.520 --> 33:22.957
- We're still trying to figure
out where the screwup was,

33:23.001 --> 33:24.828
but when his mother
was arrested,

33:24.872 --> 33:26.569
that information never
made it to us.

33:26.613 --> 33:27.657
- Right, so what's
gonna happen to him?

33:27.701 --> 33:29.746
- He has no other family.

33:29.790 --> 33:31.835
I'm afraid our hands are tied.

33:31.879 --> 33:34.360
He'll be processed into
the system tomorrow,

33:34.403 --> 33:37.580
which is a shame.
I've been going over his files.

33:37.624 --> 33:40.148
He's a good kid.
Smart.

33:40.192 --> 33:42.803
Mom's been in and out
of jail his whole life,

33:42.846 --> 33:44.935
but he had a social worker

33:44.979 --> 33:47.416
who'd been keeping him
on the straight narrow.

33:47.460 --> 33:49.766
They had a bond.
One of those relationships

33:49.810 --> 33:51.072
we all hope for.

33:51.116 --> 33:52.682
She died last year.

33:52.726 --> 33:55.816
I don't think Isaac
got over it.

33:55.859 --> 33:58.079
- Wait, his social worker
died last year?

33:58.123 --> 34:00.342
[foreboding music]

34:00.386 --> 34:03.432
- Can you tell us her name?

34:03.476 --> 34:06.957
- Abby Nicolette.

34:07.001 --> 34:09.699
- Abby Nicolette,
Ray's wife.

34:09.743 --> 34:12.311
That's the connection.

34:19.274 --> 34:21.450
- [grunts, exhales]

34:21.494 --> 34:23.148
- The lady we spoke to said

34:23.191 --> 34:25.106
they had a pretty
close relationship.

34:25.150 --> 34:27.500
- That's why he's been
acting out this past year.

34:27.543 --> 34:31.852
Abby was the only person who
ever really cared about him.

34:31.895 --> 34:33.680
He never got over losing her.

34:33.723 --> 34:36.117
- I know that feeling.

34:36.161 --> 34:39.033
- So she never mentioned him?

34:39.077 --> 34:41.166
- No, not--not by name.

34:41.209 --> 34:44.865
Uh, she talked a lot about
a kid that was really special,

34:44.908 --> 34:47.041
like a survivor.

34:47.085 --> 34:48.912
She was determined to keep him
out of the system

34:48.956 --> 34:50.349
and make sure he had
a stable life.

34:50.392 --> 34:52.829
He have any other family?
- No.

34:52.873 --> 34:54.788
And with his mother in prison,

34:54.831 --> 34:58.270
the system is exactly
where he's headed.

34:58.313 --> 35:01.055
He needs someone, Ray.

35:01.099 --> 35:03.013
[ominous music]

35:03.057 --> 35:04.972
- What, you mean me?

35:05.015 --> 35:06.408
I'm not equipped
to take in some kid.

35:06.452 --> 35:07.888
Come on.
What--

35:07.931 --> 35:09.846
- I think there's a reason
we were sent your name.

35:09.890 --> 35:11.979
And you cannot deny
the connection between you.

35:12.022 --> 35:14.068
- Abby was the social worker.

35:14.112 --> 35:16.418
She was the one who
connected with people.

35:16.462 --> 35:17.941
I'm a--I'm a ex-cop.

35:17.985 --> 35:20.770
I got a freezer
full of TV dinners.

35:20.814 --> 35:23.860
Look, I understand this kid
ain't got anybody, but I am not

35:23.904 --> 35:26.080
your answer.
I'm sorry.

35:26.124 --> 35:28.648
- Cara said that you
still talk to your wife.

35:28.691 --> 35:31.172
[solemn music]

35:31.216 --> 35:32.913
♪

35:32.956 --> 35:35.307
What do you think she
would tell you to do?

35:35.350 --> 35:42.357
♪

35:49.973 --> 35:52.802
- Well, I met Isaac.

35:52.846 --> 35:54.891
[chuckles]

35:54.935 --> 35:59.026
What're you doing to me, Abby?

35:59.069 --> 36:02.029
[sighs]

36:02.072 --> 36:04.510
Is this your answer?

36:04.553 --> 36:08.253
♪

36:08.296 --> 36:11.081
Tell me what to do.

36:15.956 --> 36:17.784
- Oh, this is about
your wallet.

36:17.827 --> 36:19.220
I've got bigger problems.

36:19.264 --> 36:21.875
- We spoke to Social Services,

36:21.918 --> 36:24.573
see if we can help you out.

36:24.617 --> 36:28.490
Are you sure you don't have any
extended family somewhere?

36:28.534 --> 36:31.276
An aunt, an uncle, someone
that we can track down?

36:31.319 --> 36:32.581
- No, there ain't.

36:32.625 --> 36:34.322
It's just me and my mom,

36:34.366 --> 36:36.933
when she was around.

36:36.977 --> 36:39.022
Why do you two care about this
so much anyway?

36:39.066 --> 36:40.285
- Because they're
annoying people,

36:40.328 --> 36:43.418
but they do grow on you.

36:47.117 --> 36:48.510
[exhales deeply]

36:48.554 --> 36:50.991
We haven't been
properly introduced.

36:51.034 --> 36:53.080
- You came all the way down
here to tell me your name?

36:53.123 --> 36:54.864
- [chuckles] Yeah,
as a matter of fact,

36:54.908 --> 36:57.911
that's exactly what I did.

36:59.608 --> 37:01.001
I'm Ray Nicolette.

37:01.044 --> 37:02.698
I believe you knew
my wife Abby.

37:02.742 --> 37:05.701
[stirring piano music]

37:05.745 --> 37:08.051
♪

37:08.095 --> 37:10.445
She ever mention me?

37:10.489 --> 37:13.143
- Maybe.
So what?

37:13.187 --> 37:15.102
♪

37:15.145 --> 37:16.669
Yo, why are you here, man?

37:16.712 --> 37:17.931
I mean, you ain't
nothing to me.

37:17.974 --> 37:19.672
- Hey, maybe not.

37:19.715 --> 37:23.241
But I think Abby wanted
you and I to meet.

37:23.284 --> 37:26.200
So I'm gonna talk
and you're gonna listen.

37:26.244 --> 37:28.289
Okay?

37:28.333 --> 37:30.117
♪

37:30.160 --> 37:31.510
[exhales deeply]

37:31.553 --> 37:34.208
I have an empty room
in my place.

37:34.252 --> 37:36.079
It's not much, nothing fancy,
but I'm guessing

37:36.123 --> 37:38.734
it beats the hell out of
wherever Social Services

37:38.778 --> 37:42.042
is planning on sending you.

37:42.085 --> 37:44.436
But

37:44.479 --> 37:46.133
there's something very
important

37:46.176 --> 37:49.745
you need to understand
if we are to move forward.

37:49.789 --> 37:52.226
- What's that?

37:52.270 --> 37:55.447
- I've been a Giants fan since
before you were born.

37:55.490 --> 37:57.971
So yeah, that Jets hat,
gonna be an issue.

37:58.014 --> 38:01.191
[acoustic guitar music]

38:01.235 --> 38:08.242
♪

38:08.808 --> 38:10.549
- Hey, we have to head out.

38:10.592 --> 38:13.029
I just wanna say it's really
nice what you're doing here.

38:13.073 --> 38:14.988
- Uh-huh, guess we'll see, huh?

38:15.031 --> 38:16.424
- Can I ask you a question?

38:16.468 --> 38:18.252
What made you
change your mind?

38:18.296 --> 38:19.993
- I know you don't believe in
this sort of thing,

38:20.036 --> 38:22.169
but two days ago I'm over on
Bow Bridge

38:22.212 --> 38:24.345
and feeling sorry for myself,
I start talking to Abby

38:24.389 --> 38:27.392
about how alone I am,
how lost I am without her

38:27.435 --> 38:30.090
because she was
my purpose in life.

38:30.133 --> 38:32.135
Without her, I don't know what
the hell I'm doing,

38:32.179 --> 38:36.183
so I asked her,
send me a sign.

38:36.226 --> 38:39.578
[chuckles]
And the next day

38:39.621 --> 38:43.495
you two showed up.

38:43.538 --> 38:46.367
- Hey, call me if you two
need anything.

38:46.411 --> 38:49.022
I do not want you having
TV dinners every night.

38:49.065 --> 38:50.763
- [chuckles]
Okay.

38:50.806 --> 38:54.767
- [laughs]
- Okay. Not a hugger.

38:54.810 --> 38:55.811
♪

38:55.855 --> 38:59.032
- See ya.
- Bye.

38:59.075 --> 39:00.773
You two make a good team.

39:00.816 --> 39:02.078
- [chuckles]

39:02.122 --> 39:05.473
- It's more rare
than you think.

39:05.517 --> 39:09.390
- ♪ So much pride
and so much fire ♪

39:09.434 --> 39:11.436
- [exhales deeply]

39:11.479 --> 39:14.482
- ♪ So much emotion
in a passing feeling ♪

39:14.526 --> 39:16.092
♪ So many things

39:16.136 --> 39:17.790
- Uh.

39:17.833 --> 39:20.880
Thank you for doing this.

39:20.923 --> 39:22.751
♪

39:22.795 --> 39:26.364
- Seriously, kid, you gotta
do something about this hat.

39:26.407 --> 39:28.757
- ♪ 'Cause we need to

39:28.801 --> 39:33.240
♪ Change

39:33.283 --> 39:34.894
[cell phone buzzes]

39:34.937 --> 39:39.246
♪ Change

39:39.289 --> 39:43.250
♪ We can change

39:43.293 --> 39:45.687
♪

39:45.731 --> 39:48.777
- Cara, I just finished
reading your new piece

39:48.821 --> 39:50.257
about the P.I.
and the pickpocket.

39:50.300 --> 39:51.693
Nice job.

39:51.737 --> 39:52.868
- Thank you.

39:52.912 --> 39:54.522
- Whatever you're doing,
keep it up.

39:54.566 --> 39:56.655
That promotion's in sight.

39:56.698 --> 40:03.705
♪

40:06.055 --> 40:08.406
[door knocks]

40:08.449 --> 40:10.799
- Hope it's not too late.

40:10.843 --> 40:13.846
- No, no, please,
come on in.

40:18.198 --> 40:20.809
Hey, is everything okay?

40:20.853 --> 40:24.857
- Yeah, as a matter of fact.
Um...

40:24.900 --> 40:28.077
I took your advice.
Spoke with your sister.

40:29.078 --> 40:30.819
Thank you.
- Yeah, no problem.

40:30.863 --> 40:33.039
- She also told me that I
occasionally put out a vibe

40:33.082 --> 40:36.608
that certain subjects
in my children's lives

40:36.651 --> 40:38.305
are off limits.

40:38.348 --> 40:40.568
- [chuckles]
Yes, I'm very familiar.

40:40.612 --> 40:42.178
- Mm.

40:45.573 --> 40:47.923
There is something

40:47.967 --> 40:49.751
I've never shared
with your sister.

40:49.795 --> 40:53.015
Um, anyone, actually.

40:53.059 --> 40:55.801
Something that happened
after Ali came out.

40:55.844 --> 40:57.324
- What?

40:57.367 --> 40:58.978
- People who were with me
from the beginning,

40:59.021 --> 41:00.936
people who were friends,
people whose children

41:00.980 --> 41:04.026
I had baptized,
whose parents I'd laid to rest,

41:04.070 --> 41:06.812
decided they could no longer
attend my church,

41:06.855 --> 41:09.728
that they could no longer
worship under the leadership

41:09.771 --> 41:13.079
of a man who had the audacity
to accept his daughter

41:13.122 --> 41:17.083
for who she is
and love her for it.

41:17.126 --> 41:19.477
- You're telling me those
people left because of Ali?

41:19.520 --> 41:20.913
- Yeah, they did.
I mean,

41:20.956 --> 41:22.958
you know, it happened over
several months,

41:23.002 --> 41:24.830
so Ali never realized
the timing,

41:24.873 --> 41:27.572
but in the end,

41:27.615 --> 41:32.185
I lost almost a quarter of my
congregation

41:32.228 --> 41:33.839
[snaps fingers]
just like that.

41:33.882 --> 41:35.057
Gone.

41:35.101 --> 41:36.537
I mean, I gotta tell ya,

41:36.581 --> 41:38.452
it scared the living hell
out of me.

41:38.496 --> 41:41.020
I mean, I have dedicated my
life to building that church,

41:41.063 --> 41:43.544
so to lose so many people
in so short a time?

41:43.588 --> 41:45.546
Mm-mm.

41:45.590 --> 41:47.200
- So what did you do?

41:47.243 --> 41:49.202
[Oliver Riot's
"Ivory Black" playing]

41:49.245 --> 41:50.943
- Nothing.
- Mm [stammers]...

41:50.986 --> 41:53.162
Sundays are standing room only.
You had to do something

41:53.206 --> 41:55.121
to get those people back.
- I wish I had.

41:55.164 --> 41:57.253
I mean, one of
my great regrets

41:57.297 --> 41:59.865
is that I was unable
to reach them

41:59.908 --> 42:01.388
to change their minds.

42:01.431 --> 42:02.650
- So what happened?

42:02.694 --> 42:04.304
- New people started
to show up.

42:04.347 --> 42:07.176
People who wanted to hear
from a reverend and a father

42:07.220 --> 42:10.615
who had the belief that faith
is something that unites us

42:10.658 --> 42:12.704
rather than divides us.

42:12.747 --> 42:15.576
And the people that left,
I don't know,

42:15.620 --> 42:18.361
maybe they did me a favor,

42:18.405 --> 42:21.277
made way for the people
I was supposed to reach

42:21.321 --> 42:24.324
who were ready
for a new message.

42:24.367 --> 42:26.326
- So why are you
telling me this?

42:26.369 --> 42:30.199
- Mm-mm-mm.
It's a good story.

42:30.243 --> 42:34.508
- ♪ Suffering sweet like
sickness scarred to a laugh ♪

42:34.552 --> 42:38.773
♪ She's my witness
starting to crack ♪

42:38.817 --> 42:40.122
♪ Ivory black

43:12.938 --> 43:14.200
- Greg, move your head.

43:14.243 --> 43:15.549
- I have an idea.
